Oh, of course.

20:33.366 --> 20:41.340
Don't forget the flop.

20:41.341 --> 20:42.208
Quebec city.

20:42.209 --> 20:44.142
One of the oldest European

20:44.143 --> 20:52.143
settlements in north America.

20:53.052 --> 20:55.521
Samuel Dechanplain sailed up the

20:55.522 --> 20:57.889
Saint Lurns and founded
the site in 1608.

20:57.890 --> 20:59.358
When the fighting started with

20:59.359 --> 21:01.159
you know who Quebec city was the

21:01.160 --> 21:02.328
French stronghold until the

21:02.329 --> 21:04.496
bitter end when the French fell

21:04.497 --> 21:12.497
at the plains of Abraham.

21:14.474 --> 21:16.542
The French may have lost that

21:16.543 --> 21:22.381
one but some things French
have stayed firm, unbowed,

21:22.382 --> 21:26.518
resiliently unchanged
by trends or history.

21:26.519 --> 21:30.255
The continental is the kind
of place about which I am

21:30.256 --> 21:33.492
unreservedly sentimental.

21:33.493 --> 21:35.394
When I was younger I ate here

21:35.395 --> 21:37.195
with my grandparents
and parents.

21:37.196 --> 21:39.531
The best restaurant in town.

21:39.532 --> 21:42.368
Classic.

21:42.369 --> 21:45.103
Unironic cuisine, meaning dishes

21:45.104 --> 21:50.742
you haven't seen
since, like, forever.

21:50.743 --> 21:55.581
Fresh, continental, ocean liner

21:55.582 --> 21:57.416
classics such as... Ceasar

21:57.417 --> 21:58.950
salad, tossed fresh to order.

21:58.951 --> 22:00.386
Table side.

22:00.387 --> 22:02.588
And beef char char also prepared

22:02.589 --> 22:08.527
table side as one must.

22:08.528 --> 22:10.362
Shrimp cocktail.

22:10.363 --> 22:14.065
A shrimp cocktail the way
Jesus wants you to eat them.

22:14.066 --> 22:19.037
All served by a
dedicated professional.

22:19.038 --> 22:21.039
In culinary school
we were taught this.

22:21.040 --> 22:23.208
Real customers is
your final class.

22:23.209 --> 22:26.211
We'd have to do the fruits,

22:26.212 --> 22:26.979
table side, all that which would

22:26.980 --> 22:28.747
fly off the fork and
land in somebody's soup.

