Bite with my teeth.

22:35.588 --> 22:36.456
Stripping the thing.

22:36.457 --> 22:38.156
At least once a day.

22:38.157 --> 22:39.591
One of the students would set

22:39.592 --> 22:44.095
themselves or the
customers on fire.

22:44.096 --> 22:46.398
The inferno would spill
and they'd light it.

22:46.399 --> 22:47.266
There would be this line from

22:47.267 --> 22:50.736
the thing down across
the floor up their leg.

22:50.737 --> 22:50.937
No.

22:50.938 --> 22:52.137
That doesn't happen here.

22:52.138 --> 22:53.939
Like I said, professionals.

22:53.940 --> 22:56.975
This is going to go
like a big fire ball.

22:56.976 --> 22:58.009
Fire ball.

22:58.010 --> 22:58.277
Good.

22:58.278 --> 22:59.478
The kind who know how to

22:59.479 --> 23:06.117
properly prepare these dishes.

23:06.118 --> 23:06.453
Sweet.

23:06.454 --> 23:08.520
Like a goose bump moment.

23:08.521 --> 23:08.788
Yeah.

23:08.789 --> 23:13.759
For Dave, another classic.

23:13.760 --> 23:17.262
A sauce made of cognac, cream.

23:17.263 --> 23:17.964
That is nice.

23:17.965 --> 23:20.265
Look at that.

23:20.266 --> 23:28.266
And for Fred, scampi Newberg.

23:28.975 --> 23:29.476
Awesome.

23:29.476 --> 23:30.276
Absolutely awesome.

23:30.277 --> 23:34.546
For me, that most noble
of dishes, Dover sole.

23:34.547 --> 23:36.381
This appears to be one of the

23:36.382 --> 23:37.649
few remaining servers alive who

23:37.650 --> 23:38.984
knows how to take that fish off

23:38.985 --> 23:46.124
the bone, sauce it, and
properly serve it.

23:46.125 --> 23:50.128
Thank you very much.

23:50.129 --> 23:52.130
So happy.

23:52.131 --> 23:54.566
Very comforting.

23:54.567 --> 23:59.905
There is continuity
in this world.

23:59.906 --> 24:07.906
Across town, another
thing entirely.

24:12.652 --> 24:20.652
The younger, wilder
affaire cech ocech

24:25.264 --> 24:33.264
cech ketchup which
means everything is cool.

24:33.706 --> 24:37.543
Are they hipsters or am I just

24:37.544 --> 24:40.178
crazy and thinks anybody
below 30 is a hipster?

24:40.179 --> 24:42.748
I don't know but I admire them.

24:42.749 --> 24:44.850
So how much did it cost
you when you opened?

24:44.851 --> 24:45.718
Not much.

24:45.719 --> 24:49.755
Look at this tiny electric
four burner stove.

24:49.756 --> 24:51.056
At no point in my cooking career

24:51.057 --> 24:52.924
could I have worked with one of

24:52.925 --> 24:53.693
these without murdering everyone

24:53.694 --> 24:55.293
in the vicinity before hanging

24:55.294 --> 24:59.798
myself from the nearest beam.

24:59.799 --> 25:01.800
How long did it take to adapt.

25:01.801 --> 25:03.234
I would say three months.

25:03.235 --> 25:05.036
In the beginning I was lucky I

25:05.037 --> 25:07.138
didn't have a lot of guests.

25:07.139 --> 25:09.608
I was like oh, man.

25:09.609 --> 25:11.810
I was freaking out.

25:11.811 --> 25:13.244
And yet these kids today.

25:13.245 --> 25:14.279
Look at them go.

25:14.280 --> 25:16.915
Serving a wild Liam Bishs and

25:16.916 --> 25:19.084
quite substantial ever changing

25:19.085 --> 25:22.788
menu out of this, this
Suzy home maker oven.

25:22.789 --> 25:27.659
Tonight there's razor clams
and a cream of haddock.

25:27.660 --> 25:30.729
Very cool.

25:30.730 --> 25:31.097
Thank you.

25:31.098 --> 25:34.766
I love clams.

25:34.767 --> 25:36.968
And you'll notice that nobody in

25:36.969 --> 25:41.006
Quebec seems to
skimp on portions.

