Head cheese with mustard.

25:44.510 --> 25:46.745
Oh, and truffled sweet breads.

25:46.746 --> 25:53.819
And some goose hearts
for good measure.

25:53.820 --> 25:54.153
Excellent.

25:54.153 --> 25:55.121
Hearts in general.

25:55.122 --> 25:59.157
Also you got your
grilled tomato bread.

25:59.158 --> 26:05.864
That's salt cod for you Anglos.

26:05.865 --> 26:08.767
I'm all swollen up like the tire

26:08.768 --> 26:12.904
dude and ready to burst
on the directional mist.

26:12.905 --> 26:15.642
Hotel/motel time for me.

26:30.489 --> 26:34.660
How Canadian is Quebec?

26:34.661 --> 26:36.828
Are they truly one
entity or two?

26:36.829 --> 26:38.664
This is a question that has been

26:38.665 --> 26:43.835
wrestled with for sometime.

26:43.836 --> 26:46.004
Question Quebec
is certainly part

26:46.005 --> 26:49.875
of Canada but in many ways
another thing entirely.

26:49.876 --> 26:52.744
There is a lot of history
much of it contentious.

26:52.745 --> 26:54.579
Go back far enough, and you get

26:54.580 --> 26:58.750
a clearer picture of why.

26:58.751 --> 27:00.085
The French arrived on the shores

27:00.086 --> 27:04.055
of Quebec city in the early 16th

27:04.056 --> 27:05.523
century and seccumbed to the

27:05.524 --> 27:07.492
military might of Great
Britain in the mid 18th.

27:07.493 --> 27:09.761
Thus began a gradual but steady

27:09.762 --> 27:12.864
persecution of all
things French.

27:12.865 --> 27:14.700
The Quebecwa have struggled

27:14.701 --> 27:16.034
mightily to hang on to their

27:16.035 --> 27:17.502
French heritage and language.

27:17.503 --> 27:19.537
The issue of seceding entirely a

27:19.538 --> 27:25.110
notion that persists to
some extent even today.

27:25.111 --> 27:26.745
Journalist Patrick la gas meets

27:26.746 --> 27:27.946
me for lunch to help me

27:27.947 --> 27:30.081
understand a little bit of what

27:30.082 --> 27:34.052
many Quebecwa feel is at stake.

27:34.053 --> 27:38.356
I was going to talk about the
whole history, identity,

27:38.357 --> 27:39.291
separatist movement but I have

27:39.292 --> 27:45.764
to get right to the
pressing matter of the day.

27:45.765 --> 27:46.132
Pastagate.

27:46.133 --> 27:47.532
What do you want to know?

27:47.533 --> 27:51.803
For those not up on current
Quebec politics, pastagate

27:51.804 --> 27:53.705
refers to an incident where

27:53.706 --> 27:55.306
local authorities notified an

27:55.307 --> 27:57.743
Italian restaurant they were in

27:57.744 --> 27:59.377
violation of French laws because

27:59.378 --> 28:03.749
they used the word pasta
which is Italian.

28:03.750 --> 28:04.450
Okay.

28:04.451 --> 28:05.817
Stop apologizing.

28:05.818 --> 28:06.118
Okay?

28:06.119 --> 28:08.954
Don't get me wrong.

28:08.955 --> 28:11.890
I lean French, hard.

28:11.891 --> 28:16.427
I am enormously sympathetic
to the language laws.

28:16.428 --> 28:18.596
You don't think it
is preposterous?

28:18.597 --> 28:21.967
I do not but here we
have a situation.

28:21.968 --> 28:23.434
It is stupid.

28:23.435 --> 28:26.137
I agree with you completely

28:26.138 --> 28:28.106
that this province 40 years ago

28:28.107 --> 28:30.175
was in some respects
an English city.

28:30.176 --> 28:33.578
We needed to have language
laws for signage and stuff.

28:33.579 --> 28:35.814
Now, signage for instance

28:35.815 --> 28:39.851
must by law be
principally in French.

28:39.852 --> 28:41.787
French first in all things.

28:41.788 --> 28:43.688
But every bureaucracy produces

28:43.689 --> 28:44.790
by products of stupidity.

28:44.791 --> 28:45.591
That was it.

28:45.591 --> 28:46.358
You know what?

28:46.359 --> 28:47.859
It will not stand.

28:47.860 --> 28:50.328
The Anglo Canadian treated

28:50.329 --> 28:52.998
French speaking Quebec law like

28:52.999 --> 28:54.532
second class crap for
much of history.

28:54.533 --> 28:55.533
I get it.

28:55.534 --> 28:56.968
I'd want my own thing and when I

28:56.969 --> 28:58.269
got it I'd want to make sure

28:58.270 --> 29:04.009
there is no back sliding
to the bad old days.

29:04.010 --> 29:05.877
The first sovereign to be

29:05.878 --> 29:08.947
elected in 1976, it didn't
come out of a vacuum.

29:08.948 --> 29:14.352
It came out from a couple
decades of awakening and

29:14.353 --> 29:14.686
struggle.

29:14.687 --> 29:16.321
50 years from now will people

29:16.322 --> 29:18.556
still be speaking predominantly
French in Montreal?

29:18.557 --> 29:19.025
Yes.

29:19.025 --> 29:19.959
No doubt about it.

29:19.960 --> 29:22.560
French first is something
most would agree with.

29:22.561 --> 29:24.963
How far and how vigorously you

29:24.964 --> 29:30.869
want to go with that, well,
do you think there is any

29:30.870 --> 29:35.073
possibility or real majority

29:35.074 --> 29:37.843
plurality who would have voted

29:37.844 --> 29:44.816
in separate nation status?

29:44.817 --> 29:47.986
In English you guys say
timing is everything.

29:47.987 --> 29:51.656
The timing was never
better than in 1991, 1992.

29:51.657 --> 29:52.891
From 1995 this country came

29:52.892 --> 29:54.392
inches from being broken up.

29:54.393 --> 29:55.861
Do you think it will happen

29:55.862 --> 29:57.929
in the history of the world?

29:57.930 --> 29:58.930
I don't know.

29:58.931 --> 29:59.931
But I know one thing.

29:59.932 --> 30:01.900
Anybody who says separatism is

30:01.901 --> 30:03.902
dead in this country and
this province is a fool.

30:03.903 --> 30:07.205
No matter how you feel about

30:07.206 --> 30:08.739
Quebec, either separate from or

30:08.740 --> 30:10.842
as essential part of greater

30:10.843 --> 30:13.344
Canada, any reasonable
person loves this place.

30:13.345 --> 30:17.082
Correct me if I'm wrong.

30:17.083 --> 30:19.350
This is famous for the
sandwich special.

30:19.351 --> 30:22.720
What tradition
does this fall in?

30:22.721 --> 30:23.754
Basically eastern Europe.

30:23.755 --> 30:24.956
It was a survival thing.

30:24.957 --> 30:26.124
It was because they were poor.

30:26.125 --> 30:29.928
And that's what they could make.

30:29.929 --> 30:32.931
Wilensky's an old school

30:32.932 --> 30:35.800
corner institution around since

30:35.801 --> 30:37.468
1932 serving up pressed meat,

30:37.469 --> 30:39.470
bologna, and salami sandwiches

30:39.471 --> 30:40.939
or specials as they call them

30:40.940 --> 30:45.410
with egg Greens and milk shakes.

30:45.411 --> 30:50.081
So the special and an
appropriate beverage.

30:50.082 --> 30:51.416
Very happy.

30:51.417 --> 30:53.718
Here's how it goes.

30:53.719 --> 30:57.088
There are rules.

30:57.089 --> 31:00.058
The special is always
served with mustard.

31:00.059 --> 31:01.659
It is never cut in two.

31:01.660 --> 31:03.261
Don't ask why.

31:03.262 --> 31:04.130
Just because.

31:04.131 --> 31:07.632
That's the way it's
always been done.

31:07.633 --> 31:10.268
A little respect for
tradition, please.

31:10.269 --> 31:11.003
Hum.

31:11.004 --> 31:14.605
I'm happy now.

31:14.606 --> 31:16.407
Some things are beloved
institutions for a reason.

31:16.408 --> 31:20.145
This is delicious.

31:20.146 --> 31:23.549
Thank you.

