You celebrate Canadian

33:41.220 --> 33:43.221
ingredients in a way
that no one else has.

33:43.222 --> 33:44.955
Are you some kind of patriot?

33:44.956 --> 33:49.060
Is that what's going on here?

33:49.061 --> 33:50.628
Is it national...
Very much a patriot.

33:50.629 --> 33:52.297
I say it all the time.

33:52.298 --> 33:54.232
This is one of most important

33:54.233 --> 33:57.668
restaurants to me in north
America if not the world.

33:57.669 --> 34:04.442
An art installation if
you actually look at it.

34:04.443 --> 34:11.181
The meal begins with a
power of maple desserts.

34:11.183 --> 34:12.250
Good lord.

34:12.251 --> 34:14.485
Sponge maple toffee, maple

34:14.485 --> 34:17.255
donuts, beaver tails,
maple cotton candy.

34:17.255 --> 34:17.755
But wait.

34:17.757 --> 34:19.324
There's more.

34:19.324 --> 34:22.327
Almond croissant,
whipped biscuits.

34:22.328 --> 34:23.094
Some nugget.

34:23.094 --> 34:23.329
Yeah.

34:23.329 --> 34:24.029
Ah.

34:24.029 --> 34:24.663
There we go.

34:24.664 --> 34:26.331
I think that is a first for me.

34:26.331 --> 34:27.864
I've never seen that done.

34:27.866 --> 34:33.170
Not with a hammer.

34:33.172 --> 34:37.007
Then let the madness begin.

34:37.007 --> 34:38.275
Next, a whole lobe of baked

34:38.277 --> 34:42.179
beans on a pan cake cooked
in duck fat of course.

34:42.181 --> 34:45.216
Cottage cheese and eggs
cooked in maple sirup.

34:45.217 --> 34:45.784
Wow.

34:45.784 --> 34:47.016
That's awesome.

34:47.018 --> 34:49.954
There's a healthy salad.

34:49.955 --> 34:51.489
Sauteed duck hearts, gizzards

34:51.489 --> 34:53.358
and pig's ear topped with a

34:53.359 --> 34:55.560
heaping pile of
fried pork rinds.

34:55.561 --> 34:58.196
Good lord.

34:58.197 --> 35:01.566
Oh, and a calf brain and
maple bacon omlete.

35:01.567 --> 35:02.168
And these.

35:02.169 --> 35:03.301
How this is made?

35:03.302 --> 35:04.069
With love.

35:04.070 --> 35:05.336
With love.

35:05.337 --> 35:09.006
Panko-encrusted duck drum

35:09.007 --> 35:10.708
sticks with shrimp and salmon

35:10.709 --> 35:12.377
moose and maple barbecue sauce.

35:12.378 --> 35:13.644
Good lord.

35:13.645 --> 35:13.845
Wow.

35:13.846 --> 35:18.649
This is a classic dish.

35:18.650 --> 35:23.921
It is a meat pie.

35:23.922 --> 35:29.227
Calf brain, sweet breads,

35:29.228 --> 35:31.262
bacon, and with Martin
that is not sufficient.

35:31.263 --> 35:33.264
Usually there is no
truffle but I just...

35:33.265 --> 35:35.333
Yes, black truffles.

35:35.334 --> 35:36.601
More truffle.

35:36.602 --> 35:38.870
Too much truffle.

35:41.240 --> 35:44.041
My blood is getting thicker
as I look at that.

35:44.042 --> 35:45.676
Now the main course, a home

35:45.677 --> 35:47.111
grown smoked right out front

35:47.112 --> 35:49.347
local ham, with pineapple
and green beans almandine.

35:49.348 --> 35:50.848
And with chicken, but with

35:50.849 --> 35:57.622
Martin, chicken is
never just chicken.

35:57.623 --> 35:59.257
Stuffed with foie
gras and lobster.

35:59.258 --> 36:01.426
We pump lobster bisque
into the chicken.

36:01.427 --> 36:03.127
Good god.

36:03.128 --> 36:11.128
There is a light at the
end of the tunnel.

36:11.903 --> 36:16.241
Oh.

36:16.242 --> 36:17.275
Someone should be singing the

36:17.276 --> 36:20.411
national anthem now,
I mean, really.

36:20.412 --> 36:24.415
In practically prehistoric

36:24.416 --> 36:25.150
old-schooled Canadian classic,

36:25.151 --> 36:26.484
maple syrup is heated, then

36:26.485 --> 36:31.155
poured on snow, making a kind of

36:31.156 --> 36:32.790
Taffy, but the preferred

36:32.791 --> 36:38.829
delivery mechanism does
present some issues.

36:38.830 --> 36:40.097
No, no, no, no, no.

36:40.098 --> 36:40.632
What?

36:40.633 --> 36:42.967
Take a big one, and
you have to suck it.

36:42.968 --> 36:47.438
Don't swallow it, you know?

36:47.439 --> 36:49.940
Look, you have to go like
that, slowly, slowly.

36:49.941 --> 36:52.009
You know?

36:52.010 --> 36:54.945
Just slowly, slowly.

36:54.946 --> 36:57.348
That's how it's good.

36:57.349 --> 36:59.250
That's it.

36:59.251 --> 37:02.086
Can I do that in a manly way?

37:02.087 --> 37:03.688
You just sort of look
away in a distracted way.

37:03.689 --> 37:11.689
I'm not really... the
best way is to look up.

37:14.800 --> 37:17.635
Finally maple meringue cake
and maple ice cream with

37:17.636 --> 37:22.707
chocolate shards.

37:22.708 --> 37:24.442
Any suggestion on
how to attack it.

37:24.443 --> 37:25.510
We did it once.

37:25.511 --> 37:32.483
I went the chef suggests a cone

37:32.484 --> 37:35.720
and the chef suggests
you eat it like that.

37:35.721 --> 37:36.388
There's the thing.

37:36.388 --> 37:37.356
I think there's too much

37:37.357 --> 37:44.495
focusing on the food, wow, these

37:44.496 --> 37:45.530
are very intellectual and wow.

37:45.531 --> 37:46.731
I've done too much of
all those... you know?

37:46.732 --> 37:47.399
I don't want to do that.

37:47.400 --> 37:53.338
I don't want to play
games any more.

37:53.339 --> 37:57.909
Because food is
feces in waiting.

37:58.710 --> 37:59.710
This is CNN.

38:11.189 --> 38:12.423
If there's one thing you
always need on a cold snowy

38:12.424 --> 38:15.326
night, it's yet
another hearty meal.

38:15.327 --> 38:21.165
I meet back up with Dave and the

38:21.166 --> 38:22.867
Liverpool house, sister
restaurant to Joe beef.

38:22.868 --> 38:24.435
I think we always compensate

38:24.436 --> 38:27.572
a little bit with
overabundance of food.

38:27.573 --> 38:29.507
Because of our insecurity of not

38:29.508 --> 38:31.376
being, like, good cooks.

38:31.377 --> 38:33.778
You know what?

38:33.779 --> 38:35.513
It's a combination of low

38:35.514 --> 38:36.947
self-esteem and generosity that

38:36.948 --> 38:39.717
explains the amount
of food, perhaps.

38:39.718 --> 38:45.723
First course... gravlax of char.

38:45.724 --> 38:49.527
Salman gundi.

38:49.528 --> 38:50.396
Beets and eggs.

38:50.397 --> 38:51.397
Look at that.

38:51.398 --> 38:53.130
Unbelievable.

38:53.131 --> 38:57.201
Look at the aspic work.

38:57.202 --> 38:59.504
This is smoked potatoes inside.

38:59.505 --> 39:01.472
Salmon pastrami.

39:01.473 --> 39:02.073
Wait a minute.

39:02.074 --> 39:09.580
This is super classic.

39:09.581 --> 39:12.450
Soft, boiled or poached egg

39:12.451 --> 39:15.620
in clear gelatin broth classly

39:15.621 --> 39:19.056
garnished with white ham,
tarragon leaves and black

39:19.057 --> 39:19.591
truffles.

39:19.591 --> 39:20.392
Oh, my god, I was pretty sure

39:20.392 --> 39:21.159
I would live the rest of my life

39:21.159 --> 39:21.960
without ever seeing this again.

39:21.961 --> 39:24.161
Delicious.

39:24.162 --> 39:27.632
But tonight after a full week of

39:27.633 --> 39:33.604
Franco-Canadian full-on assaults

39:33.605 --> 39:36.941
on our livers and our lights,

39:36.942 --> 39:39.444
Fred and Dave thought it would

39:39.445 --> 39:42.913
be good to take advantage of the

39:42.914 --> 39:45.015
insanely delicious fare by their

39:45.016 --> 39:46.951
brilliant chef Omar,
who's from Pakistan.

39:46.952 --> 39:48.453
Amazing, authentic
Pakistani food.

39:48.454 --> 39:51.822
What do we have here?

39:51.823 --> 39:58.429
Butter chicken crab, tikka,
pomegrana pomegranate.

39:58.430 --> 39:59.697
A little mushrooms.

39:59.698 --> 40:02.833
Rabbit korma.

40:02.834 --> 40:09.139
Fingerlings with a
fenugreek and fennel.

40:09.140 --> 40:11.208
This is donkey hanarri.

40:11.209 --> 40:14.011
Yes, he did say donkey.

40:14.012 --> 40:14.546
The dishes continue.

40:14.546 --> 40:15.313
Pakistani gumbo with okra and

40:15.314 --> 40:18.483
coriander, a says my seed
and green pepper curry.

40:18.484 --> 40:23.320
Hangar steak, scotch egg, and an

40:23.321 --> 40:26.190
authentic goat biryani.

40:26.191 --> 40:26.658
Wow.

40:26.659 --> 40:28.459
Biryani's awesome.

40:28.460 --> 40:28.894
Are you full?

40:28.894 --> 40:29.828
Yeah.

40:29.829 --> 40:31.361
Pretty close.

40:31.362 --> 40:35.032
We did good work here.

40:35.033 --> 40:37.702
In the end, and perhaps as a nod

40:37.703 --> 40:42.206
to the Anglo tradition,
however, there will be stilt.

40:42.207 --> 40:46.677
This is a genius meal.

40:46.678 --> 40:51.482
These princes of gastronomy,

40:51.483 --> 40:53.217
never a suboptimal moment.

40:53.218 --> 40:58.889
Nothing short of
excellent accepted.

40:58.890 --> 40:59.924
Beyond excellent.

40:59.925 --> 41:00.859
Too much excellent?

41:00.859 --> 41:01.226
Yes.

41:01.226 --> 41:01.560
Possibly.

41:01.560 --> 41:01.993
Over the top?

41:01.994 --> 41:03.260
Yeah, definitely.

41:03.261 --> 41:04.062
It all comes around in the end.

41:04.063 --> 41:05.996
The circle of life.

41:05.997 --> 41:08.833
We begin at the beginning, the

41:08.834 --> 41:15.272
heart and soul of every
right-thinking Quebecois,

41:15.273 --> 41:15.674
apparently.

41:15.675 --> 41:18.776
Ice, a stick, and a puck.

41:18.777 --> 41:20.210
Fred and Dave and Martin Picard

41:20.211 --> 41:21.912
are joined by the original god

41:21.913 --> 41:23.848
of Montreal gastronomy, the

41:23.849 --> 41:27.518
great chef Norman la Pris to

